title: For Sale:  PTR 91 GI - New In Case and Unfired
postcontent:
I've wanted this rifle for years, and finally ordered it directly from the PTR Industries factory in Aynor, SC in mid-September.  They built it for me, and I finally took delivery...just days after the flood that destroyed swaths of the city and damaged much more (my home included).  Given the situation, my wife coerced me - at great cost to our relationship - to try and sell the rifle so we can have additional funds for the repairs we need to make to our home.

If you're looking for a PTR 91, you already know what you're getting...virtually the best non-licensed HK91 "clone" there is; produced on a combination of original HK tooling and improved tooling designed by PTR Industries themselves.  You won't find a more solid, reliable rifle than this...guaranteed.  (Literally.  The buyer can take advantage of the transferable 2-year end-to-end warranty (with about 23 months left at this point), assuming you feel like paying a $20 transfer/registration fee to the company.  Of course that does not include the already-applicable lifetime warranty on any internal components manufactured by PTR Industries...which are most of them.)

Again, I knew when I received it that I would need to try and sell it, so I have not fired it.  In fact, I have not even removed it from the case other than to drool over it and wish life wasn't so unfair!  

These rifles fetch a premium, and they are worth it.  However, I know that there are some online stores that sell this model for MUCH less than other stores - hundreds less than you can buy them locally, or even used from Cabela's; a smidgen less, in fact, that I paid after a tough negotiation with PTR Industries; shipping; and the transfer fee.  So, given that it IS a new rifle, I am pricing it at exactly what I have in it (apart from 2 boxes of ammo, which you can have for free if you are local).  That may be a hair more than the lowest sale price you can find online, but it breaks even once you pay transfer fees...and it's a person-to-person sale (if you are local).  

If you disagree with my rationale for the pricing, feel free to try and convince me...but bear in mind that this is probably the cheapest PTR 91 you will EVER find...and I had to do the negotiation to make it so.

title: For Sale:  AR15 with lots of extras.
postcontent: This little beauty is a 16" barreled 5.56/.223.  The lower is an Aero Precision brand with Magpul Stock and Magpul Grip. The fire control group is powered by a JP trigger complete with reduced power spring kit. The fun doesn't end there! An short throw ambidextrous safety selector (The Gavel) is just one of many "extras" on this gun. Ares Armor provided the lower parts kit.  An oversized billet trigger guard allows for continuous firing even while wearing gloves. On top of that, the rear takedown pin is oversized and has a hole in it to accept a ring, paracord, or whatever else you might want to add in assisting removal for cleaning and maintenance. One last note on the lower.  Under the grip is a set screw with a nylon buffer on it.  By mounting the upper and then  screwing this down until it bumps the upper, you can then expect a tight lockup between receivers and better overall accuracy. Cool aye?  The upper half of this handsome devil is anchored by a Quentin Defense upper, a Nickel Boron BCG, and a BCM Gunfighter charging handle with a large latch for easy, one handed charging with a mounted scope. The barrel is fitted with a Kaw Valley Precision muzzle device and shrouded by a Seekins Precision free float quad rail handguard. The gun has seen less than 20 rounds and that's only because I only had time to test for reliability and a brief accuracy test. It is easily holding sub MOA at 100 yards. As the barrel is broken in I would expect it to stay that way and actually improve. This began as a project to use the extra parts I already had on hand  and blossomed into a very enjoyable build.  Selling to make space for more; and I want to build a pistol. Will sacrifice for 800 and I'm pretty solid on that number.  Im going to kick in 60 rounds of ammo as well to get you off on the right foot. Not particularly interested in trades at this time, but since your already reading this, and since 98% of the members of these groups are allergic to cash, you may as well make your trade offers visible and I'll consider them. Thanks in advance.
